Let’s be honest – who here doesn’t love sushi? I could eat it daily although I don’t need or want that much rice every week. Which is why this low-carb, 100% plant-based rainbow cucumber sushi is the perfect compromise! I’ve shared options similar in my story for years but this is awesome! By @alphafoodie

Full recipe below, send it to a friend who’d love this!⁣…By @buzzfeedtasty 
 
Ingredients (for 2 servings)
2 cups brown rice (390 g)
2 cups vegetable broth (475 mL)
2 carrots, diced
1 tablespoon oil
½ white onion, diced
2 cloves garlic, minced
½ cup frozen peas (75 g)
salt, to taste
pepper, to taste
2 eggs, whisked
scallion, sliced, for garnish

Preparation
Add the brown rice, vegetable broth, and diced carrots to your Instant Pot. Stir until combined.
Close the lid until you hear the beep. Tip: Closing the lid can be tricky. Have the pressure knob at 11 o’clock and turn right.
Turn pressure knob to “Sealing”. Select Manual and reduce the time to 24 minutes. It will say “On” in a few seconds. Note: the Instant Pot will need to warm up for 5-10 minutes. Steam will be released and a few minutes later, the time will start counting down.
Once the time goes off, carefully turn the pressure knob to “Venting”. Let all of the stream release before opening the lid.
Stir the rice, then transfer from the pot into a medium sized bowl and set aside.
Select “Saute” on the Instant Pot. Once it says “Hot”, add the oil.
When the oil is shimmering, add the onion. Cook for around 1 minute until slightly opaque.
Add the minced garlic, frozen peas, salt, and pepper. Mix until incorporated.
Add rice mixture and stir until everything is combined.
Make a well in the middle of the rice for the eggs. Pour the beaten eggs into the well, stirring only the eggs until they are cooked.
Mix everything together. Top with scallions.
Enjoy! 
 
#friedrice #rice #egg #veggies

Who would eat this meal?! 
 
A bowl of Green Bean and Mushroom Stir-Fry with a very sad amount of rice 😂—but don’t worry I had way more rice than what was photographed here 👀🍚…By @thefoodietakesflight

Alsooo it’s another new week?! It’s the last full week of May (where did the time go?!) and this is one of those weeks when I need to make a conscious effort to sit down and actually sort through the countless photos and videos I need to edit this week. 😅

I love what I do but I’m a one-man show so there are days when I feel so overwhelmed—espcially as I’m sitting on weeks worth of content and I just keep cooking & shooting more. 🙈 but so excited to share more recipes in the coming weeks hehe.

ANYWAY, this is a really simple yet tasty stir-fry wit some blistered green beans and fresh mushrooms cooked in a homemade stir-fry sauce. The thick sauce is perfect to be scooped over some rice or noodles. 🥢

Strawberry shortcake bar(dairy-free) 

Recipe below by @wholesomehedonista 
 
Recipe (Makes 5) 
Ice cream base 
1 cup canned coconut cream (chilled/unshaken - use the thick white cream on top only discard liquid - brands can taste different I use Thai Kitchen) 
1/3 cup maple syrup 
2 teaspoons vanilla 
1 tablespoon salted cashew butter 

Blend ingredients together until smooth. Pour into silicone ice cream molds. Freeze overnight (6-8 hours). Let thaw about 3-12+ minutes (depending on how warm your house is) before coating. 

Crumb Coating 
3/4 cup gf or regular vanilla cookie crumbs (I used the  Partake birthday cake cookies my fave or I also tried it with the Catalina Crunch vanilla sandwich and those were pretty good If you’re keto)- I used about 8 little cookies total 
1/2 cup freeze dried strawberries 
1 tablespoon coconut oil, melted

In a blender or food processor pulse cookies a few times until you have small crumbs. Pour half the mixture onto a plate. Then add strawberries and pulse until a fine crumb forms. Pour strawberry mixture onto the plate with the other cookie crumbs and mix. Pour the melted coconut oil on top and mix with hands until all crumbs are evenly coated. Place thawed bar into the crumbs, pressing the mixture into the bar gently with hands - you may need to flip a few times. If it’s not sticking thaw it a bit more but not too long or the bars may break in half or will take a long time to refreeze . Place coated bars on a wax paper lined tray and freeze about 20-30 more minutes or until firm again. Hope you enjoy! 

#healthydessert #vegandessert #dairyfree #healthyicecream #icecreambar #healthytreat #veganicecream #nicecream #dairyfreeicecream #strawberryshortcakeicecreambar #healthyvegandessert

Follow @laura_lambe to learn how to transform your physique and still eat your favourite foods. 
 
Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough Overnight Oatmeal 🍪🍪🍪

Hop aboard the Overnight Oat train with THIS delectable recipe!…By @cleanfoodcrush

"Soaked" oats save a lot of time in the morning, but they’re also much easier to digest than unsoaked oats.

As the oats soak overnight, their digestibility greatly improves, here's how:

Overnight as they soak, the starches break down which improves digestibility and the natural phytic acid (which all plants contain) is greatly reduced that makes them more easily absorbed by your body!

Yes. These oats are meant to be eaten cold like pudding.

➡️Rachel's notes:
Use any dark chocolate chips of your choice: the higher cacao percentage, the better.

If you're looking to keep sugars lower; try Lily's brand chocolate that is sweetened with stevia. 

Use ANY milk of your choice. My personal preferences for these oats are unsweetened coconut milk, or cashew milk. 

I often add protein or collagen powder to my overnight oats. If you choose to do this, then your oats my need an extra splash of milk.

4-6 servings

Ingredients:

2 cups old fashioned rolled oats
2 cups milk of choice
1 cup Greek yogurt
1/2 cup dark mini chocolate chips
2 tsps vanilla extract
pinch of sea salt
good pinch of ground cinnamon
1/2 cup almond butter, or cashew butter 

Instructions:

Add all of your ingredients except for almond butter/cashew butter into a large bowl and whisk or stir really well to combine.

Cover and refrigerate for at least 6 hours to overnight.

Once your oatmeal has set, remove from the fridge and quickly fold in the almond/cashew butter. You don't have to completely mix it in, leave in some visible swirls!

Transfer your oatmeal to individual jars or bowls and serve.

Or keep refrigerated for a quick breakfast for up to 3-4 days. 
 
#oats #overnightoats #oatmeal #oatmealbowl

Follow @bodysmartfitness for the best fitness tips! 
 
Chicken Teriyaki Fried Rice 🍚 
Full recipe below, send it to a friend who’d love this!⁣…By @buzzfeedtasty
 
Ingredients (for 4 servings)
* 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts, cubed
* 1 cup teriyaki sauce (240 mL)
* 2 teaspoons oil
* ½ cup onion (75 g), diced
* 1 tablespoon garlic, minced
* ½ cup carrot (60 g), diced
* 1 cup broccoli floret (150 g)
* 3 eggs, beaten
* 3 cups brown rice (690 g), cooked
* 2 tablespoons soy sauce
* 1 tablespoon sesame oil
* pepper, to taste

Preparation
1. Marinate the chicken in teriyaki sauce in the refrigerator for at least an hour. 
 
2. In a wok or deep skillet, add the chicken in the teriyaki marinade and cook thoroughly over high heat. Set aside. 
 
3. In the same pan, add the oil and cook onions, garlic, and carrots until onions are translucent.
4. Add broccoli and cook an additional 3-4 minutes. Push all of the cooked vegetables to the side of the pan. 
 
5. Beat the eggs and pour into the cleared half of the pan. Scramble the eggs and mix with the rest of the vegetables. 
 
6. Add rice, cooked chicken, soy sauce, sesame oil, and pepper. Mix well and let the rice cook until slightly crispy. 
 
7. Enjoy!
 
#stirfry #healthymeals #teriyaki #chicken #rice #foodplan #foodie #veggies

Follow @kittywufitness to learn how to achieve your dream bod WITHOUT diets or giving up delicious foods like this! 😍👙

Can’t seem to get rid of those sweet cravings?! Here’s a healthier yet mouthwatering alternative…the SIMPLE BAKE CINNAROLL! 😛 Only 5 simple ingredients in only 5 mins! (1 serving)…Made by @sunnysrecipes 

To make the DOUGH: 
2-3 tbsp Greek yogurt 
1 tbsp honey
1/4 cup self rising flour 

FILLING:
1 tsp of your favorite melted coconut oil 
Cinnamon & brown sugar 

HOW TO:
Make dough by mixing dough ingredients together and thoroughly kneading, add flour as needed.
Flour your surface and roll the dough out until it’s nice and pretty 😍 
Use a brush to spread coconut oil over the dough.
Press the cinnamon & brown sugar mix into your dough.
Making a vertical cut, cut the dough into two strips.
Roll the dough up into your cinnamon rolls!
Place in your favorite mug and microwave for 90-120sec until ready (drizzle with honey or a bit of powdered sugar if you like) …and ENJOY 😉
